<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Imgur Gallery</title><link>https://imgur.com</link><description>description</description><lastBuildDate>2022-07-05 16:20:41.617012</lastBuildDate><item><title>Husband and I didn't agree politically</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/IwxmWsQ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/F2ERLEj.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Back story: Husband and I are high school sweethearts. Been together 11 years, married almost 3 years. We have twin 1 & 1/2 year olds, a boy and girl. My family has not been untouched by the darkness in the world. At 4 years old I was raped by my father. At 14 years old I was raped again by a masked man who was never caught. That rape resulted in a pregnancy that could have killed me. Before I had to make the choice to have an abortion, I miscarried the fetus. Just the miscarriage left me in the hospital for a long while. (Caused a lot of health complications) was told then I'd never have kids. That year I met my then boyfriend. 
Fast forward to fall of 2019 just before COVID: We got married and by January we were pregnant and excited. (I have always been very political, I always vote even for the small town elections. My husband is not very political and never really talks about it.) I started bringing up political things because now I have children. I want the world to be better for them. Find out my husband and his family are all Trump supporters. I started feeling scared and depressed that I got married into a potentially bad/dangerous family. Worried that my husband would be okay with the abortion ban. I was worried about bringing up the topic. But I know I want to live in a safe state for my family. 

Brought up the topic and he Surprised me by showing me all the research he is doing about what states or pro-choice and that he is looking into jobs in each state and is even talking about potentially trying to move to Canada.

***Update*** I forgot to say, my husband is no longer a Trump supporter, ever since we had our daughter. Thankfully he is no longer listening to his Father on political issues. (Not because I forced any of my views on him. I am a big believer of everyone having their own opinions, no matter how wrong they are/s.)

Also we intend to wait to make any decisions until the end of the year. We plan to vote in the upcoming elections and see where things are and then make a plan. 

I want to thank everyone for the advice and up votes! Stay weird imgur!

**Update #two** It baffles my mind that in 6 hours over 100,000 people saw this post I thought would die in usersub as all my other posts have. Thank you for your comments, your advice and the free internet points!

**Update #3** I was worried that I would cause an argument by bringing up the topic of moving. I was raised by a single mom who believes that women aren't supposed to have a voice or opinions. So I've always had a hard time expressing myself around family or loved ones. My husband has been working on helping me be more expensive and talking about things but it is still something I struggle with. He is a good man and only wants the best for my twins and I.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wbdqah5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/am7nwxi.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ACIJaFs.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The last few things that made me chuckle</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/IwxmWsQ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Savage9613]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Professor X Games</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Rg9pWp0</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lD3U85w.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It's new to me</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Rg9pWp0</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[RomeoEightJuliet]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Something something stomping a mudhole has a new meaning</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/iMxnHsE</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Tl0IqN5.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/iMxnHsE</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MuffledGorillaViolence]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Oldest host in the park</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/5mo19BZ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EeJvrwA.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>When I was 14 years old, I was abused by an older man. It went on for years. I am now 31 years old. I tucked the trauma into a corner of my mind and never spoke about it. 

Last week, I found out that this man is still abusing girls. Saying the same things to them, grooming them the same way. I found a 14 year old girl that was abused two months ago. 

I feel like the oldest host in the park. And I have a responsibility to protect other girls. 

I have an appointment with a lawyer next week in order to start a criminal investigation into this man. 

I'm going to stop him.

Support/encouragement would be appreciated?

Edit: Fuck wow, thank you thank you for the outpouring of support. It breaks my heart how many similar stories there are out there. I wish I could hug every single one of you. I also wish I could post the asshole's name and where he lives, without the threat of a libel suit. (Even thought it's 100% true, that's the world we live in.) DM me if you have more advice, or just want to talk. It's a relief knowing I'm not alone. And now it kinda feels like I have an Imgur army behind me. Thank you so much.

Edit2: https://me2csa.com/ is a site for adult survivors of abuse to anonymously identify their abusers. If an abuser has been named by more than one survivor, they will be notified. I just submitted, and I encourage others to do the same. Without being able to name our abusers publicly, this is the best shot we have in finding other victims and coming forward together.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/5mo19BZ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[HowDoesOneWeaveASigourney]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I’m sure many of my other non-US Imgur friends feel the same way</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/huphuoP</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MGSiSyT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/huphuoP</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[beclamide]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Identity Theft is a very serious crime, Jim.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/L6XlkKM</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/s845KZ9.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/L6XlkKM</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[RoachTypePerson]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I bet it really ties the room together</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/KPVS6i8</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/joTAxuF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Udz8sdb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I'd buy it

